# Runtime configuration for the fleet supervisor.
# Edit via `fleet config set <key>=<value>`. The supervisor re-reads this
# file periodically and applies changes without restart.
# In-flight subprocesses are NEVER killed by a config change.
#
# telegram_chat_id: Telegram chat/channel ID for supervisor notifications.
#   Empty string (default) disables Telegram notifications.
#   The bot token is supplied via the TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN env var (never stored here).
#
# telegram_allowed_ids: Comma-separated numeric Telegram user/chat IDs that may
#   create fleet tasks by messaging the bot with /task commands.
#   Empty string (default) disables the inbound listener entirely (default-deny).
#   Example: "123456789,987654321"
#
# telegram_default_cwd: Working directory assigned to tasks created via Telegram.
#   Empty string (default) leaves cwd unset on the created task.
